The article is a statement from the White House Press Secretary regarding the Adam Smith Amendment. The President applauds Adam Smith for his leadership in closing the detention facility at Guantanamo Bay. The amendment aims to eliminate restrictions on transferring detainees and move past this chapter in US history. The Administration objects to statutory restrictions that impede closing the facility and pursuing appropriate options for detainees. The statement highlights the success of federal courts in terrorism-related cases and calls for Congress to lift remaining restrictions. The President threatens to veto the Defense Authorization bill if unwarranted restrictions remain.